KEY INSIGHTS FROM DISCUSSION

Network vs. Tree Understanding
Team member stated: "A network means a single line has multiple variations of values. A decision tree means one line represents one probabilistic value."

This is the fundamental distinction driving all technical decisions.

Circular Networks are Acceptable
Papers reviewed showed networks that were not strictly hierarchical (had circular paths). This validated the team's complex structure.

One Line, Multiple Probabilities
The breakthrough understanding that connections cannot have single probabilities changed approach significantly. This explains why CPT tables exist separate from connection lines.

Probability Formula Discovery
Team identified formula structure for CPT calculation and recognized it involves multiplication of probabilities, aligning with Bayesian probability theory.

